We are home!!! 😍 As I mentioned recently, I'm taking time at the moment to really think about my goals for next year. I will be doing an Instagram story explaining a bit more about this, but I set my main goal and then I work out how I’m going to GET IT DONE!⁣
⁣
I don’t set a generic goal, I make it really specific, and then plan in detail. If I say I’m going to get stronger, I then figure out: how many times a week I’m going to train, which program I’m going to do, what time I’m going to train, who’s going to look after Arna while I’m at the gym and when is the best time to eat around my workouts. Every day this needs extra planning too - I need to have all my gym clothes ready, my water bottle and my bag. I make sure I have EVERYTHING I need to be successful, rather than having a vague goal and just hoping somehow I'll get there. ⁣
⁣
What are YOUR goals for the next year? Have you joined the SWEAT Challenge? Let’s start 2020 STRONGER TOGETHER! 💪🏼

In Australia so many families celebrate by getting outdoors, having barbecues or picnics. If you're spending a lot of time with loved ones, this is a BENCH workout you can do with a friend of member of your family to get active together over the holiday season! ⁣
⁣
✅ Bench Jump - 30 seconds⁣
✅ Incline Mountain Climber - 30 seconds⁣
✅ Snap Push-Up - 30 seconds⁣
✅ Snap Jump & Knee-Up - 30 seconds⁣
✅ Tricep Dip - 30 seconds⁣
⁣
The goal is to do a full lap of this superset without a break, and complete each superset three times!⁣
⁣
www.kaylaitsines.com/app⁣

This is the difference between Christmas in Australia and Christmas in the northern hemisphere! When I was in the US a few years ago, I realised how Christmas is celebrated there with carols, snow and decorations everywhere. It’s incredible to me because Christmas is usually such a hot day in Adelaide and I can’t even imagine it snowing, but I know it’s so different in every part of the world. I want to know, how do you celebrate at this time of year? Comment below!⁣

I don't stop training when I'm on holidays! I feel most confident after smashing out an amazing workout, so why wouldn't I want to continue to feel like that during my holiday break?! A 'break' to me doesn't mean not going to the gym. A break is taking time off work, spending more time with my family, eating meals together and relaxing by the pool. I can still do ALL of that AND work out, too! BONUS. My workouts when I'm on holidays are only ever 30 minutes so they don't take up too much of my day. I am honestly SO grateful to be able to work out again, having regained my strength after having a baby. I never want a day in my life (unless pregnant, sick or post-pregnancy) where I'm not active in some way!!💪Holiday gym workouts? YES PLEASE!

#BBG #BBGstronger

Find the exercise that's right for YOU!!! If you’ve been following me for a while, you might already know that I’m not a big fan of running. In my opinion, there’s nothing wrong with running - it just doesn’t work for me. I don’t enjoy it and I don’t feel great afterwards. If you are doing any type of exercise because you think it will get results, but you actually don’t enjoy it, I would recommend changing it up.  Mostly because if you don't like it, you're less likely to keep doing it. ⁣
⁣
From my experience as a personal trainer, you are more likely to stick to an exercise program if you enjoy it and feel GREAT after - that’s why BBG workouts are 28 minutes - I try and keep them fun and fast. The LISS (low-intensity steady state) workouts in BBG are a chance for you to do a form of exercise that you really enjoy. ⁣
I recommend starting with walking if you are a fitness beginner because I find it's most achievable for many women when starting out. I love walking because it’s something I can do with Arna in a stroller and it gets us both out of the house. If I'm not able to get out for a walk with Arna, I'll walk on the treadmill and watch Netflix! 😁⁣
⁣
If you want to try different types of LISS, I recommend hiking, cycling (outdoors or on a spin-cycle bike), swimming - or anything that can be done at a steady state for 30-45 minutes. ⁣
⁣
Finding out what works for YOU is KEY. I really want women to train and start their health and fitness journey from a place of self-love, not doing a form of exercise they dislike because they feel like they “have to”. Having a positive relationship with yourself and your training is SO important, so if you actually LOVE running, keep doing it! ⁣
But if you haven’t found what you love yet, keep trying until you do! And the #BBGcommunity will be there to support you the whole way! 💪🏼🙌🏼

OMG I DID IT🙌🙌🙌🙌 I’M SO PROUD!! ⁣If you've been following my journey since having Arna, you'll know that I have been working towards a goal of 15 pull-ups by December! ⁣
⁣
To be honest - I don’t actually care that it’s 15 pull-ups, because at the end of the day, it’s not about how many pull-ups I can do, or how far I can run or how high I can jump - the fact is I showed up for myself EVERY SINGLE DAY. I put in the work, and I did this for ME, just to prove to myself that I could. By regaining my strength, I also regained my CONFIDENCE. ⁣
⁣
This has actually been a HUGE learning process for me, because I never thought I would be a "beginner". From being such an active kid to becoming a personal trainer, there was never a day in my life when I wasn’t active, so I literally never thought I wouldn’t be able to move the way I was used to moving, but that’s exactly where I was. ⁣
⁣
#BBGcommunity, I could not have done this without you. Your support, your inspiring stories - I am where I am today because of you. It's so important for all of us to continue to set NEW goals throughout our health and fitness journeys. Ladies, I want to know - what YOU are working towards? Share your goals in the comments below!

I was really struggling but I kept pushing through and I felt like I was really held accountable by knowing they would see it. Although it might look easy, it really wasn’t AT ALL. I’m so PROUD to be where I am today - it’s been a lot of hard work and sacrifice and it’s so worth it! 💪🏼

Reflecting on 2019 makes me SO happy! It’s been amazing for us - I can’t believe it included having Arna, being able to do a bootcamp in Dubai, and the release of 2 new programs! This year has been incredible and I can’t wait for 2020. I’m so glad to be able to do this with my best friend, the person who makes me the happiest, the father to our sweet baby girl - @tobi_pearce I love you so much and I’m so proud of you! 😍💞

I have spoken a lot about my personal journey recently and my goal of completing 15 pull-ups by December. ⁣What you might not know is what truly motivates me to work so hard towards this goal is YOU. Seeing members of the #BBGcommunity achieve such incredible results, showing up for themselves day after day and supporting one another. THAT is what gets me up and into the gym, that is what inspired me to push through when I was feeling tired or defeated.⁣
⁣
I wanted to prove to myself and others that you just have to SHOW UP for yourself, and put in the time and effort. Even if you’re not feeling motivated that day, there is always someone out there that’s going through something similar to you, or can inspire you. That’s what drove me to get out of bed every day and try a bit harder. I could have easily given up that day when I couldn’t even do one pull-up, but instead I showed up, day after day. Not just for myself, but for the Community - to show YOU what’s possible. To some of my biggest inspirations from the BBG Community: @fit.mum.melbourne @syd_journey  @onehappyfitmum @lella.fit @Radish34tulip @bananabreadtoburpees @mari.pitkanen THANK YOU!!! Now it’s almost 2020 and I feel like we can ALL take on the world! 💪🏼🙌🏼👊🏼⁣
